Package com.nsl.web.net

Class HttpsRequest<D>

java.lang.Object
com.nsl.web.net.HttpsRequest<D>
Direct Known Subclasses:
HttpsRequestBinary, HttpsRequestHtml
public abstract class HttpsRequest<D> extends Object
Given URL from the client, an object responsible to send a request to the URL. It would be better if you call HttsRequest.request() out of main thread.
Author:
PGD

    • storeData

      protected abstract DataContainer<D> storeData(HttpsURLConnection conn, boolean isSuccess) throws IOException
      Defining how to store data to DataContainer object. Given a connection to the URL, take InputStream from the connection, and get data through the stream.
      Parameters:
      conn - instance which connects
      isSuccess - true if building connection was successful, false if building connection failed, according to the response code.
      Returns:
      a data container which contains the resource.
      Throws:
      IOException - is thrown if there is some problem in the InputStream received from HttpsURLConnection.
